kodkod.cli

Class StandardKodkodOutput

  • java.lang.Object
    • kodkod.cli.StandardKodkodOutput
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    KodkodOutput

    public final class StandardKodkodOutput
extends java.lang.Object
implements KodkodOutput
    An implementation of the KodkodOutput interface that writes solutions provided to it to standard output, in the form of s-expressions. Given a satisfiable solution s, an instance of this class will produce output of the form (sat :model ([ri {(int+)*}]*)), where each ri is a relation in s.instance, and {(int+)*} is an s-expression representation of the tupleset s.instance.tuples(ri). Each tupleset is represented as a list of tuples, and each tuple is represented as a (space-separated) list of atom indices comprising that tuple.

    Given an unsatisfiable solution s to a problem p, this implementation will produce output of the form (unsat :core (fi+)), if a core is available, or of the form (unsat), otherwise. Each fi is a formula identifier in p.env.defs['f'] such that the formula p.env.defs['f'][fi] is in s.proof.highLevelCore().values(). If there are some formulas that are in the core but are not defined in p.env.defs['f'], a warning message will be printed to a specified logger.

    For both sat and unsat solutions, a StandardKodkodOutput instance prints all statistics as info messages to its logger. The format of the info messages is unspecified.
